<SLUG> BC-TECH-MEDIA01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TECH MEDIA:Technology has criminal appeal
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News ServiceIn print
<TEXT>
<P>
   As the Internet has grown in popularity, so has its appeal to
criminals. They're using it increasingly to steal, defraud and
conduct scams. All is not lost, though. There are plenty of ways to
protect yourself. Many of the methods are described in the
September issue of PC World. The magazine describes how to foil
hackers and thieves, block junk e-mail and scams and protect your
credit card number.
</P>
<P>
   Check out some of the latest games in the September issue of PC
Games. You'll find reviews of 45 new games, including ``Unreal,''
``Final Fantasy VII,'' ``Descent: Freespace,'' ``X-Com:
Interceptor'', ``Hardball 6'' and ``X-Files.'' The magazine also
offers strategy tips and cheat codes for ``Unreal,'' ``Forsaken,''
``Dark Omen'' and ``Cyberstorm 2.''
</P>
<P>
   On CD-ROM
</P>
<P>
   Broderbund has released the latest addition to its line of clip
art libraries. This one features 8,500 color and black-and-white
images of famous art. It includes watercolors, drawings, oil
paintings and landscapes. There are also 200 photographs.
``ClickArt Fine Art'' is available only for Window PCs. It retails
for $29.95.
</P>
<P>
   One of the most popular new characters for young kids is Blue, a
dog of that color who stars on a PBS show. He has now come to
computers, and his latest game is called ``Blue's Birthday
Adventure.'' In this game, you get Blue ready for his birthday
party. Kids create a personalized birthday card for Blue, select a
special present for him and solve new puzzles. The game is
available for both Macs and PCs.
</P>
<P>
   Online
</P>
<P>
   If you're interested in volcanoes, here's a hot place to learn
about them on the Web. It's called Volcanoes Online and features
all kinds of information about this geological phenomenon. There
are also games that let you play with the information you've
learned. You'll find this site at
http://despina.advanced.org/17457/.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
