<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   TITANIC-MIDNIGHT _ A report from the poop-ed deck. We go behind
the scenes at a store that's staying open all night 8/31-9/1 to see
just how intense the demand for that damned video was. (Vejnoska,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   TITANIC-VIDEO _ Will our level of curiosity over the RMS Titanic
ever sink? Apparently, not yet. Monday August 31, at midnight,
videocassettes of Titanic _ the most financially successful movie
in history, which re-creates the maiden voyage of the least
successful ocean liner of all time _ go on sale. (Erstein, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ALLMAN-BROTHERS _ ATLANTA _ Advancing the Allman Brothers Band
concert this night (8 p.m. Tuesday), which kicks off a five-show
stand at the Fox Theatre. The band last played there almost exactly
20 years ago. We talk to Gregg Allman about what the group is
calling a ``homecoming,'' plus others. (Dollar, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   DUPREE-SHOW _ SOCIAL CIRCLE, Ga. _ We head to Social Circle to
see the newly renovated Victorian home of Georgia cook Nathalie
Dupree, whose new PBS cooking series (shot this year in the house's
stunning new kitchen) begins tonight on GPTV. Dupree's cooking
series is going national this season and already media outlets
(including USA Today, People and NBC's ``Today'') will have stories
on her and her home (renovation was completed this summer) in
September. We write about the home, the show and what Dupree is
feeding us for lunch. (Longino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
PHOTOS. ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   NEWSSTAND _ Highlights from the periodicals. (O'Briant, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   PAXSON _ If PAX TV works, Bud Paxson, 63, becomes a billionaire,
a media power broker running with the Michael Eisners and Rupert
Murdochs of the world. And he will have done what no one else has
ever done: Create a network dedicated to G-rated shows and built
primarily with stations he owns _ not affiliate stations, which is
how other networks work. (Lomartire, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
