<P>
   RUSSIA-CLINTON _ MOSCOW _ Viktor Chernomyrdin's chances of
becoming Russia's new prime minister appeared dim on Monday after
most parliamentary parties came out against him in a first
confirmation debate in the State Duma lower house. Sergei
Reshulsky, a senior Communist official, said before the start of
the debate that Chernomyrdin, prime minister between December 1992
and March 1998, was unlikely to garner more than 120 votes,
including those of his own party, a few dissident Agrarians,
Russian Regions deputies and independents. Will also analyze the
day's events in the context of President Clinton's scheduled
arrival in Moscow Tuesday. We lay out and explain the agenda for
the summit with President Boris Yeltsin, and the character of the
U.S.-Russia relationship. Developing. (Holmes, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-BOX _ MOSCOW _ A primer on Russia. (Holmes, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: To move by 4 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   MISSILE-POLICY _ WASHINGTON _ Documents obtained by The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution and interviews with officials in the Reagan,
Bush and Clinton administrations show that Republicans were just as
aggressive as Democrats in removing commercial satellites and other
high-tech equipment from a list of exports controlled by the State
Department known as the Munitions List. (Carr, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TRYPTOPHAN _ WASHINGTON _ Mayo Clinic researchers report finding
low levels of a potentially harmful contaminant in off-the-shelf
samples of a popular dietary supplement, 5-Hydroxy-L-Tryptophan
(5-OH-Trp or 5-HTP). The contaminant, called ``peak x,'' was linked
to symptoms suffered by a family exposed to 5-HTP in 1991. It also
has a similar chemical structure to contaminants found in batches
of a related supplement, L-Tryptophan, which were linked to a 1989
outbreak of eosinophilia myalgia syndrome (EMS) that affected
thousands of people. (Nesmith, Cox News Service 500).
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   GORE _ Vice President Al Gore comes to Dayton to stump for Mary
Boyle and we see how the Democratic faithful treat the second in
command. (Bebbington, Dayton Daily News). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GORE-KIDS _ Gore and Boyle take on a much younger and nicer
crowd when he has a town hall meeting in Dayton. They just may
surprise him and pepper him with questions about Clinton. (Hulsey,
Dayton Daily News). WITH PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   MLK-OFFER _ Follow on James Earl Ray's brother's offer to
release information for a price. (Brice, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NOVEMBER-BALLOT _ An unexpected retirement, a death and a
lawsuit are combining to change the November ballot considerably
since the March primaries. With two Democrats, Al Price and Dan
Kubiak, out of the race, does this change the partisan algebra?
(Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   KUBIAK _ Information on memorial services for Rep. Dan Kubiak,
D-Rockdale. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   GOV _ Texas poll on governor's race; Bush's approval rating.
(Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-LATINAS _ SAN ANTONIO _ Lena Guerrero, Nora Linares and
Christine Hernandez said they can pass on experience to other
Latinas looking to enter the world of public leadership in the next
century. Along with other Texas Latinas, the three are forming the
Latina Foundation, an organization they hope will help teach young,
ambitious Hispanic women interested in public service what they
need to know. (Gamboa, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TORT-REFORM _ TALLAHASSEE, Fla. _ The cardboard flier features
an automatic pistol, opens ominously to a warning that state Rep.
Bill Andrews refused to disarm wife beaters. For Andrews and four
other suddenly-vulnerable lawmakers, it's the unleashed vengeance
of Florida's trial lawyers, who through a front group have dumped
$371,000 worth of mailers, broadcast and ``push polls'' against the
legislators, all five of whom supported a measure limiting
lawsuits. (Date, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
