   &UR; NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   USWEST-STRIKE (Denver) _ Members of U S West Inc.'s largest
union ended their 15-day strike and began returning to work Monday
at the large phone company after reaching a tentative agreement on
a new three-year contract. The Communication Workers of America
left messages on hot lines and on the Internet late Sunday that the
roughly 34,000 strikers in 13 states should put away their picket
signs. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEW YORK &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   NY-STATE-FAIR (Syracuse, N.Y.) _ For many city slickers familiar
with state fairs only through old movies or television shows, the
annual, end-of-summer events are anachronistic bastions of quaint
pastoralism. And to some extent, that's an accurate appraisal. The
wonders of cultivation, from monstrous zucchini to mammoth swine,
are still celebrated. The divine arts of pickling, canning, cookie
baking and jelly making still win intensely coveted blue ribbons.
But while the 152nd New York State Fair includes cows being trotted
out by breeders eager to show off their livestock, it also features
llamas leaping over a gradually raised bar for no purpose other
than entertainment. By Frank Bruni. (1000 plus)
</P>
