 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story
SCI-DIABETES-GROWTH (a) by Marie Sanches, which moved Aug. 24, will
wish to use the following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A Boston Globe article on diabetes mischaracterized the status
of 12-year-old Jake Dunigan, who is in a diabetes prevention trial
at the Joslin Diabetes Center &UR;  &LR; in Boston. Jake is at risk of
developing Type 1 diabetes, but has not developed the disease. His
father, Jay Dunigan, does have Type 1 diabetes. In addition, Dr.
Gordon Weir's experiments on transplanting insuling-producing cells
are being conducted in animals, not patients.
</P>
