<HEADLINE>
HOT TRAVEL DEALS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sun., Sept. 6)  
 (JT)  
 By JANET PIORKO    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   KENYA FARE SALE _ Sabena Belgian World Airlines has introduced a
sale fare to Nairobi starting at $999 round trip from New York to
help boost travel to the city following the bombing of the U.S.
Embassy there last month. The fares, which are nonrefundable, are
valid for travel from Tuesday through March 31, except for Dec. 12
to Jan. 11, when they are $200 higher. A Saturday stay is required;
the maximum stay is one month. Departure taxes and fees of $60 are
extra. The flights connect through Brussels. Reservations: (800)
955-2000. The United States Department of State lifted its travel
warning on Kenya on Aug. 13.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA DEAL _ The Delta Queen Steamboat Co. is offering air fare
at no extra cost for passengers who make a reservation by Oct. 24,
with a $300 deposit, on the Mississippi Queen's Kentucky Derby
cruise next spring. The reservation must be for a category E or
higher stateroom on the 414-passenger paddlewheeler, with rates
starting at $2,150 a person, double occupancy. The eight-night
Derby cruise from Memphis to Louisville, on April 24 to May 2,
includes seats at the race as well as festivities beforehand.
Information: (800) 543-1949; reservations are made through travel
agents.
</P>
<P>
   FALL IN IRELAND _ CIE Tours International has a four-night Taste
of Ireland trip priced from $799 a person, double occupancy, from
New York, including round-trip flights on Aer Lingus, bus
sightseeing, hotels, daily Irish breakfast and dinner, taxes and
tips. Departures are on Thursdays from Oct. 15 through Nov. 19. The
$799 price is for November; October departures are $1,051. Starting
in Dublin, the tour takes in Cashel, Blarney, Killarney, the Ring
of Kerry, the Clare coast and the Cliffs of Moher. Information:
(800) 243-8687.
</P>
<P>
   SAILING SALE _ Windjammer Barefoot Cruises has a package
starting at $680 a person, double occupancy, through Oct. 31 for a
six-day trip on the 294-foot, 122-passenger Legacy, a four-masted
barkentine once used by the French government for meteorological
research. The price includes round-trip flights from New York or
Miami on Tower Air, the six-night cruise, meals and some drinks.
The cabins are not luxurious _ they have no television or radio,
for example _ but they are comfortable, with private bathrooms, and
are air-conditioned, according to Michael Thiel, a company
spokesman. The Virgin Passage itinerary departs from Fajardo,
Puerto Rico, and visits Culebra, St. Croix, St. John, St. Thomas
and Jost Van Dyke. The Blackbeard itinerary calls at Vieques and
Virgin Gorda, rather than St. Thomas and Jost Van Dyke. Weather can
be dicey this time of year in the Caribbean, and itineraries may be
adjusted accordingly. For more information: (800) 327-2601 or (305)
672-6453.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
