<HEADLINE>
LONGER FOR FALL  
(JT)
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Spring's pleated skirt has grown longer for fall, its
hem reaching anywhere from below the knee to the floor. Just keep
in mind that those ankle-length and longer skirts are cut to fit
tall women.
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has ankle-length skirts by Philippe Adec ($195)
and Claudie Pierlot ($140) and a below-knee style by Shin Choi for
Coleridge ($175). In the Adec 2 line are pleated skirts ranging
from below-the-knee to ankle length ($146 to $158), at both
Bloomingdale's and Saks Fifth Avenue.
</P>
<P>
   Saks also has a long skirt by Susan Lazar ($450), and
Bloomingdale's has a below-knee style by French Connection ($74).
Barneys New York has below-knee skirts by Jill Stuart ($180) and
Veronique Branquinho ($425). And Macy's is offering ankle-length
skirts by ABS ($212).
</P>
<P>
   If price is no object, a floor-length pleated skirt by Marc
Jacobs ($1,185) and an ankle-length skirt by Chanel ($1,175) are at
Neiman Marcus.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
