<P>
   BBN-GALLARAGA _ ATLANTA _ The National League will rule today on
a suspension for Braves first baseman Andres Galarraga, who charged
the mound two weeks ago when he was hit by a pitch for the 22nd
time. The Braves say opposing pitchers are throwing at Galarraga.
But opponents contend Galarraga's unorthodox batting stance and
stride keep him in harm's way. (Wilkinson/Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
