   FBN-UT-STADIUM _ AUSTIN, Texas _ When the Texas Longhorns meet
the New Mexico State Aggies on the field, the average Texas fan
will encounter a bigger, prettier stadium that athletics officials
swear on their playbooks will be ready. Three shifts of
construction crews have been working around the clock for the past
three months to finish a massive renovation of Royal-Memorial
Stadium's east side, officials said. (Roser, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-SCHOOL _ After he finishes his 4 a.m. to 1 p.m. shift,
Publix stock clerk Jay Cintron goes to his home in Lantana, changes
out of his uniform, gets dressed in his workout clothes and
continues pursuing his dream. Every Sunday morning, he and about a
dozen other guys in their late teens and 20s make their way to
World Gym in Delray Beach to attend Flex Armstrong's Pro Wrestling
World Do-Jo, a school for wannabe wrestlers. (Houck, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
