<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CLINTON _ MOSCOW _ Viktor Chernomyrdin's chances of
becoming Russia's new prime minister appeared dim on Monday after
most parliamentary parties came out against him in a first
confirmation debate in the State Duma lower house. Sergei
Reshulsky, a senior Communist official, said before the start of
the debate that Chernomyrdin, prime minister between December 1992
and March 1998, was unlikely to garner more than 120 votes,
including those of his own party, a few dissident Agrarians,
Russian Regions deputies and independents. Will also analyze the
day's events in the context of President Clinton's scheduled
arrival in Moscow Tuesday. We lay out and explain the agenda for
the summit with President Boris Yeltsin, and the character of the
U.S.-Russia relationship. Developing. (Holmes, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-BOX _ MOSCOW _ A primer on Russia. (Holmes, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: To move by 4 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   MISSILE-POLICY _ WASHINGTON _ Documents obtained by The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution and interviews with officials in the Reagan,
Bush and Clinton administrations show that Republicans were just as
aggressive as Democrats in removing commercial satellites and other
high-tech equipment from a list of exports controlled by the State
Department known as the Munitions List. (Carr, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TRYPTOPHAN _ WASHINGTON _ Mayo Clinic researchers report finding
low levels of a potentially harmful contaminant in off-the-shelf
samples of a popular dietary supplement, 5-Hydroxy-L-Tryptophan
(5-OH-Trp or 5-HTP). The contaminant, called ``peak x,'' was linked
to symptoms suffered by a family exposed to 5-HTP in 1991. It also
has a similar chemical structure to contaminants found in batches
of a related supplement, L-Tryptophan, which were linked to a 1989
outbreak of eosinophilia myalgia syndrome (EMS) that affected
thousands of people. (Nesmith, Cox News Service 500).
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
