<P>
   NOVEMBER-BALLOT _ An unexpected retirement, a death and a
lawsuit are combining to change the November ballot considerably
since the March primaries. With two Democrats, Al Price and Dan
Kubiak, out of the race, does this change the partisan algebra?
(Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   KUBIAK _ Information on memorial services for Rep. Dan Kubiak,
D-Rockdale. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   GOV _ Texas poll on governor's race; Bush's approval rating.
(Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-LATINAS _ SAN ANTONIO _ Lena Guerrero, Nora Linares and
Christine Hernandez said they can pass on experience to other
Latinas looking to enter the world of public leadership in the next
century. Along with other Texas Latinas, the three are forming the
Latina Foundation, an organization they hope will help teach young,
ambitious Hispanic women interested in public service what they
need to know. (Gamboa, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TORT-REFORM _ TALLAHASSEE, Fla. _ The cardboard flier features
an automatic pistol, opens ominously to a warning that state Rep.
Bill Andrews refused to disarm wife beaters. For Andrews and four
other suddenly-vulnerable lawmakers, it's the unleashed vengeance
of Florida's trial lawyers, who through a front group have dumped
$371,000 worth of mailers, broadcast and ``push polls'' against the
legislators, all five of whom supported a measure limiting
lawsuits. (Date, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
