annual, end-of-summer events are quaint pastoralism. But while the
152nd New York State Fair includes cows being trotted out by
breeders eager to show off their livestock, it also features llamas
leaping over a gradually raised bar for no purpose other than
entertainment. By Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-DEBAKEY-SURGERY (New York) _ Dr. Michael DeBakey moved like
a dancer, anticipating his surgical partner's every move during a
quadruple bypass operation on a woman at The Methodist Hospital the
other day. What made it an extraordinary operation is that DeBakey,
the pioneering heart surgeon, turns 90 on Sept. 7. By Lawrence K.
Altman. With photo. (MOVED)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TURANDOT (Beijing) _ Staging of the opera epic Turandot in
the Forbidden City, the very setting Puccini imagined for his
Orientalist fantasy of an icy princess who succumbs to love. By
Erik Eckholm. (MOVED)
</P>
<P>
