the USWest strike and, increasingly, a given in the American
workplace. Overtime hours have increased in recent years, federal
stats show, as companies and governments cut workers and squeeze
more hours out of the employees who remain. While the practice
trims costs and increases profits, it is taking its toll on the
home lives of employees. With OTRULES and OTSIDE. By PAT FLANNERY.
