COMPUTER-COLUMN (Undated) - As the Internet has gone mainstream,
tales of how people are putting it to use are getting more
interesting.
</P>
<P>
   Take what happened a couple weeks ago at New Vision
International, a $200 million Tempe, Ariz., company that
distributes nutritional supplements around the world via a network
of 700,000 salesmen. A storm collapsed the roof of the warehouse
and headquarters building.
</P>
<P>
   Brothers Jason and BK Boreyko, who co-own New Vision,
immediately expanded their World Wide Web site, describing the
damage and cleanup efforts and reassuring distributors that orders
would be filled _ albeit a bit late. By DAVID HOYE. Story moved in
the ``F`` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
