``welfare reform'' is a corporate welfare bill that, if adopted,
will result in a wealth transfer of millions of dollars from the
pockets of ordinary Americans into the hands of large corporations
and descendants of creative authors from the distant past.
</P>
<P>
   A bill has passed the U.S. House of Representatives and is being
held up in the Senate only because other special interests are
using it as a tool to try to enlarge their own slice of the
copyright pie. By DENNIS S. KARJALA. Story moved in the ``K``
category. &QL;
</P>
