</P>
<P>
   HONGKONG-MARKET (Hong Kong) _ The Hong Kong government continued
to play cat-and-mouse with currency traders Monday _ abruptly
withdrawing from the stock market after it had feverishly
intervened last week. Without the government to prop up shares,
Hong Kong's market promptly plunged 7.1 percent. Despite the
magnitude of the decline, several analysts said the market had not
tumbled as much as they had expected. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   These stories will move by  &UR; 8:30 p.m. Eastern time &LR; :
