on Wall Street and its implications for Main Street. By Gretchen
Morganson.
</P>
<P>
   CREDIT (New York) _ As foreign and domestic investors fled to
the safe harbor of the United States Treasury market, talk was
growing of a market-calming interest rate cut by the Federal
Reserve. The surge in buying of Treasury bonds and notes came in
the afternoon, driving the yield on the 30-year bond to 5.25
percent, the lowest for long-term rates in 30 years. By Jonathan
Fuerbringer.
