<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Tuesday, Sept. 1. The N.Y. Times News Service Night
Supervisor is Pat Ryan; phone: (888) 346-9867; e-mail:
patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Waves of selling by investors large and
small engulf the stock market, erasing all of the market's gains
since the first of the year and sending stock prices down more than
19 percent from their peak just six weeks ago, the sharpest decline
in eight years. By Edward Wyatt. (We plan to move the story by 9
p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   The story will run under a 4-column, 3-line hed.
</P>
<P>
   With several graphics, including a 6-col. look at market
performance.
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-RDP (Moscow) _ Russia's parliament rejects President
Boris Yeltsin's choice for prime minister, leaving the nation
rudderless in the midst of its deepening economic crisis. By
Michael R. Gordon. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-POLICY (Undated) _ Looking at the choices ahead for
federal regulators and the Federal Reserve after the day's turmoil.
By Richard W. Stevenson. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``g''
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-ASSESS (New York) _ A news analysis of the day's events
on Wall Street and its implications for Main Street. By Gretchen
Morganson. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-ALBRIGHT (Sarajevo, Bosnia-Herzegovina) _ With her bold
public stands undermined by irresolution in the White House and her
experience rendered less relevant by new economic crises, Madeleine
Albright has had a tough 20 months as secretary of state. A look at
Albright's role in the midst of the Russia crisis. By Steven
Erlanger. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-VOICES (New York) _ Reaction from investors, analysts and
executives to the tumultuous market day. By Robert D. McFadden.
(Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
