<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves on deck: Houston Astros
 &HT;    By I. J. Rosenberg
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ When: 7:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV: Fox Sports South.
</P>
<P>
   _ Probable starting pitchers: LHP Denny Neagle (13-11, 3.62,
4-4, 4.42 ERA lifetime vs. Astros) vs. RHP Sean Bergman (11-7,
3.56; 1-3, 7.03 ERA lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   _ Notes: Neagle appears to be getting back on track, winning his
last two starts after dropping four of his previous five. He faced
Houston on May 15 and picked up a victory, going 7 1/3 innings and
allowing one run on six hits. While Neagle is 7-3 at home, his ERA
(4.47) is high. His problems continue to come between pitches
76-90, when opponents are hitting .383. The Astros are hitting .276
against Neagle. Derek Bell is 8-for-25; Craig Biggio is 5-for-26.
Bergman has seen his ERA go from 3.18 to 3.56 in the last month,
but he's been very effective for a pitcher at the end of the club's
rotation. He did get knocked around by the Braves in a start last
week in Houston, going 5 1/3 innings and allowing five runs, four
of them earned. He defeated the Braves on May 17, pitching eight
innings and allowing one run. Andres Galarraga is 9-for-16 against
Bergman, and Ryan Klesko is 6-for-11 with three home runs. The
Braves are hitting .337 against Bergman.
</P>
