Good as It Gets,'' was applauded by audiences, several studios are
looking for screenplays about ``a sympathetic patient taking on a
mean-spirited HMO,'' says U.S. News &AMP; World Report. ``The
Rainmaker'' touched on the issue, too.
</P>
