will be held September 17-21 in, of all places, Clinton, Mont.
</P>
<P>
   _ Modern Bride magazine's most romantic wedding-dress theme this
fall is ``Titanic, the trend goes on and on,'' and is that any way
to begin a marriage?
</P>
<P>
   _ Tourism officials across California _ it's a pretty tight
network, says San Francisco's  &UR; Laurie Armstrong &LR;  _ have been on the
lookout for a scam artist, but a new court order should prevent
this freeloader from striking again.
</P>
<P>
   The woman had run up room-service bills and stayed free at five
or six Los Angeles hotels after telling public-relations officials
that she was a writer working, on speculation, for the Frommer
travel guides. She'd flash a few photocopied pages from a guidebook
and say she had written them.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, although the woman did submit material to the Frommer
publishers, none of it was fit to be published.
</P>
<P>
   The gimmick wasn't nice, but it wasn't illegal, either.
Macmillan, publisher of the Frommer series, got a court order
demanding that she cut it out.
</P>
<P>
   _ The latest carry-on baggage for jet-setters, reports GQ, is a
$1,735 cashmere lap blanket that comes in a nylon carrying case
with a matching travel pillow. ``Private-jet owners are snapping
them up,'' says the magazine.  &UR; Steven Spielberg &LR;  is said to have
ordered eight.
</P>
<P>
   _ So you're riding along on your broomstick, and you look over
your shoulder, and there goes time flying by. Llewellyn's Witches
Datebook, a calendar for 1999, comes complete with magic tips,
daily planetary motions and telephone/address log.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Mark Pritchard &LR;  refers nature-loving travelers to a Web site
(www.graceidaho.com/html/sodasprings.html) for Soda Springs, Idaho,
which has the ``only captive geyser in the world. It is turned on
every hour on the hour and will reach heights up to 150 feet. North
of town along Highway 34 is the Monsanto Chemical Plant that
produces elemental phosphorous. Just south of the plant is a huge
slag pile where you can occasionally see the red-hot slag poured
out along the edges of the pile, and appear like a lava flow.''
</P>
