<HEADLINE>
POPE PUTS HIS NAME ON DESIGNER SHADES
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   A new line of designer products _ sunglasses, T-shirts, sweaters
and ``leather items'' _ carrying the signature of  &UR; Pope &LR; 
 &UR; John Paul II  &LR; will be on the market in Italy next month.
</P>
<P>
   According to British Vogue, the merchandise is being
manufactured in the south of Italy, with the approval of the pope,
as part of a subsidized effort to put the unemployed to work. A
portion of the profits will go to charity, too.
</P>
<P>
   (Vacationing in Castel Gandolfo until mid-September, the pope
told tourists on Sunday that he understood the sadness of going
back to work when vacation is over. ``But there's an antidote
against depression,'' he said. ``Keep in your heart a great ideal
of authentic values which give sense to your life.'')
</P>
