<SLUG> BC-DOW-READERBOX-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Tracking the Fall of the Dow Jones Industrial Average
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What happened?
</P>
<P>
   A: The Dow Jones industrials suffered their second-biggest point
loss ever Monday. The stock market has now lost all of its gains
for the year.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What caused it?
</P>
<P>
   A: Investors continue to fear the impact of Asia's and Russia's
economic problems on the profits of U.S. companies. They also are
cashing in on the huge appreciation of their stock holdings.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Which investors were hurt the most?
</P>
<P>
   A: Holders of technology stocks, like Austin, Texas-based Dell
Computer and Atlanta-based MindSpring, and investors in
multinationals like Coca-Cola Co.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What's next?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``There's no clear signal that we're at a bottom yet,'' says
analyst Arthur Hogan of Jefferies &AMP; Co.
</P>
