<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 22:01 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1805 &Cx1f; taf-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RUSSIA-TEXT-2NDTAKE-N     08-31 0556
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RUSSIA-TEXT-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
  
 MOSCOW: carried out.  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Grigory Yavlinsky, Leader of the Yabloko faction
</P>
<P>
   The Yabloko faction has made a unified decision on the
impossibility of supporting Viktor Stepanovich Chernomyrdin for the
post of Prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
   The reasons for making such a decision are, first, that under
Chernomyrdin, during the six years he was the Prime Minister, an
extremely inefficient economic system was created. It was under him
that the use of barter and money surrogates reached 85 percent, 75
percent of the economic turnover. It was under him that payment of
wages, pensions and social subsidies stopped and huge unemployment
emerged. It was under him that all these processes gained huge
force.
</P>
<P>
   Secondly, it was during those six years, five and a half years,
that a semi-criminal economic system was created in Russia. A
semi-criminal economic system means, for example, that even
according to our official statistics, up to 40 percent of our
turnover is in that shadow economy, which does not pay taxes.
</P>
<P>
   It means that the main sources of revenues are in the criminal
sector.
</P>
<P>
   And it is during the period of that Government that Russia
became a leading country in terms of the level of corruption. Any
child in Russia can tell you the main problem of the Russian
Government: that there are thieves there.
</P>
<P>
   That's it. These are the main three reasons why we cannot
support this candidate. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Vladimir Zhirinovsky, Leader of the ultra-nationalist Liberal
Democratic Party
</P>
<P>
   Viktor Stepanovich, if you had a powerful political structure,
they would have prepared for you the speech that I am going to
deliver on your behalf. ...
</P>
<P>
   I feel that the situation in the country is tense, and the visit
of President Clinton today is not a timely one, the more so because
his recent moral scandals, for us, people with high spiritual
qualities, do not allow us to meet with a man who cannot settle his
relations with a secretary.
</P>
<P>
   According to the traditions of Russian society, in this case he
should divorce his wife and marry the secretary, to turn this
disgraceful page over. ...
</P>
<P>
   We have other, more important issues to discuss. And moreover, I
recommended that President Clinton not hold private meetings with
the leaders of the political parties because it is a state visit. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Aleksandr Shokhin, Leader of Our Home Is Russia, Mr.
Chernomyrdin's faction
</P>
<P>
   I would like to propose the following plan to form a
``last-chance Government.'' It can be done if Viktor Stepanovich
Chernomyrdin, together with the President, comes up with a program
for Government action, promises to form an efficient Cabinet and
makes the program public.
</P>
<P>
   With these programs, which are highly important, and after
consultations during a recess, we could vote not only for the Prime
Minister but also for the nucleus of the Government team.
</P>
<P>
   And then each faction will make its judgment, not only on the
basis of oral and written documents presented by the candidate, but
also with trust in its representatives in this Government _ if, of
course, this scheme will work.
</P>
<P>
   And finally the approved Prime Minister _ no matter who wins
this approval _ will have to implement a new economic course, and
our faction wishes him, God willing, to become a Russian Roosevelt.
</P>
</TEXT>
