<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 22:03 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1808 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-PAXON-COX     08-31 0384
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PAXON-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    PAX-TV makes its debut
 &HT;    By Marguerite M. Plunkett
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Following a champagne toast by Lowell
``Bud'' Paxson, PAX TV, the nation's seventh commercial network,
was born at noon Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The launch was without glitches or surprises, according to
Paxson Communications Chief Executive Jeff Sagansky.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm glad I don't have a better story,'' Sagansky said.
</P>
<P>
   Paxson, chairman of West Palm Beach-based Paxson Communications,
PAX TV's parent, toasted the hard work of his employees and said he
is confident the family-friendly network will succeed, Sagansky
said.
</P>
<P>
   Reruns of Touched by an Angel and others, including Dr. Quinn,
Medicine Woman and Diagnosis Murder, are the foundation of the new
network, announced in November. The programming is broadcast by 95
stations owned, operated, or affiliated with Paxson, reaching 76
million households with television sets. Paxson also has cut deals
with cable TV companies to air PAX TV where the company doesn't
have stations.
</P>
<P>
   PAX TV's local station is Paxson-owned WPXP-Channel 67.
</P>
<P>
   The first advertisement to run on the network's first show _ the
Paxson-produced Great Day America _ was for AvMed health plan,
followed by Isis Prepaid Cellular. The second commercial break
included a promotion for PAX TV shows and and an ad for a Time-Life
classic music collection. Other ads in the first hour were for
South Florida Ford dealers, The Complete Runners Guide and Palm
Beach Atlantic College in West Palm Beach.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Schulman, a Boca Raton media buyer, said it's too early to
size up the network's advertising without knowing the rates that
are being paid.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's very early,'' Schulman said.
</P>
<P>
   Paxson's stock (AMEX: PAX) was off $1.06 a share Monday to close
at $9.13 _ on a day when the Dow Jones average closed down more
than 500 points.
</P>
<P>
   Sagansky suggested PAX TV could provide some comfort to market
players.
</P>
<P>
   ``After a day like today,'' he said, ``they're going to need
Touched by an Angel.''
</P>
<P>
   Headquarters: West Palm Beach
</P>
<P>
   Network: 95 stations owned, operated or affiliated with Paxson
</P>
<P>
   Reach: 76 million households
</P>
<P>
   First commercial: AvMed
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
