<SLUG> BC-FBN-JETS-ELLIOTT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JETS' ELLIOTT IS CHARGED WITH DWI AND SPEEDING
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 By GERALD ESKENAZI   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Jumbo Elliott, the New York Jets' left tackle and a key player
in the team's fortunes, was arrested at 5 a.m. Sunday not far from
his Long Island home, and charged with driving under the influence
of alcohol and speeding.
</P>
<P>
   He was released on his own recognizance and a court date was set
for next Tuesday. That is a day off for players who open the season
on Sunday in San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   The Jets declined comment Monday and Elliott could not be
reached. The Jets players were given the day off.
</P>
<P>
   Detective Lt. Kevin Caslin, of the Nassau County police
information office, said the 32-year-old Elliott was stopped in his
Mercedes-Benz and cited for driving at 80 mph in a 55 mph zone,
failure to signal and making unsafe lane changes. He was not given
a breath test.
</P>
<P>
   Caslin said Elliott was stopped on the Long Island Expressway
one exit from his home in Manhasset, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   Elliott started in Friday night's preseason finale in Chicago,
and complained of a sore ankle afterward. The Jets' players were
off Saturday but had meetings Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The charges are misdemeanors. Because Elliott has no prior
arrest record, it is possible the charges will be reduced.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-31-98 2235EDT &QL; 
