<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 22:40 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1871 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-UCLA-LADN     08-31 0143
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UCLA FRESHMAN NOSEGUARD MIGHT MISS OPENER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Second-string nose guard Ken Kocher, one of the Bruins' most
promising freshmen, is doubtful for UCLA's Sept. 12 season opener
against Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Kocher suffered a sprained/bruised right ankle Wednesday. He was
on crutches for several days and is now using a walking cast.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA's injury report lists him as day-to-day.
</P>
<P>
   ``It'd be nice if he's ready,'' defensive coordinator Nick
Aliotti said. ``But he hasn't practiced in quite a while, so I
don't think so.''
</P>
<P>
   Even if Kocher's ankle heals, he probably won't be mentally
prepared after missing vital learning time.
</P>
<P>
   ``We were force-feeding him (the defense),'' Aliotti said. ``But
with the injury, he's way behind.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
