<P>
   VIAGRA-AD-COLUMN (New York) _ Madison Avenue is answering in the
affirmative when asked ``Am I blue?'' _ not a reference to Wall
Street but to a certain little pill. That pill is of course Viagra,
the hugely popular drug from Pfizer Inc. that treats male
impotence. On the market only since April, Viagra has already made
a place for itself in the national vocabulary. Viagra's ability to
quickly become such a looming presence on the cultural landscape
has intrigued marketers and agencies, which are always seeking ways
to garner attention for what may otherwise be prosaic
advertisements. By Stuart Elliott.
